Note:
This file implements Sparse Conditional Constant Propagation (SCCP), the
Wegman-Zadeck algorithm.

SCCP simultaneously discovers:
- Which SSA values are compile-time constants (constant propagation), and
- Which CFG edges are executable (conditional-branch pruning),

using two interacting worklists over a three-level lattice
(UNKNOWN 0 -> CONSTANT 1 -> OVERDEFINED 2). It is strictly more powerful than
separate constant folding plus dead-code elimination because it considers
control flow: a branch whose condition is a proven constant only makes the
taken edge executable, so values that flow only through the un-taken edge are
never raised to OVERDEFINED and can themselves be folded.

After the fixed point:
- Every value-producing pure instruction whose result is CONSTANT is replaced
  with a fresh canonical MIR_CONST record carrying the proven value, and
- Every conditional branch whose condition is a proven constant is rewritten
  to an unconditional MIR_JUMP to the taken block, with the un-taken CFG edge
  (and the un-taken successor's phi predecessor) removed.

This file consists of:
- The lattice transition with SSA-use re-enqueueing (sccp_raise_lattice)
- The per-instruction evaluator (terminator edge enqueueing + value transfer)
- Constant binary / comparison evaluators with the canonical fold guards
- The application phase (const replacement + constant-branch folding)
- The pass-manager entry point run_sccp_pass(cfg)
:End Note

Note: ============================================================================
Note: IMPORTS
Note: ============================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/mir.runa" as MIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/mir_nodes.runa" as MIRNodes
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/cfg.runa" as CFG
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/ordered_map.runa" as OMap
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: USE MAP - value id -> List of instructions that use it
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "build_use_map" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Builds the pass-local SSA-edge structure SCCP needs: value id -> List of
    instructions that USE that value. The raise of a value's lattice fact must
    re-enqueue exactly the instructions that read it (that is what makes the
    algorithm SPARSE), and SSA construction does not materialize MIRValue
    use-lists (Wave 4), so the only authoritative source is the instruction
    stream itself. Integer keys mandate an ordered map - collections/dictionary
    string-hashes integer keys and crashes at runtime (Wave 3).

    For every instruction, every used value (header operands, phi incomings,
    and call/invoke arguments, all enumerated through
    CFG.get_instruction_used_values plus the call-argument list) gains this
    instruction in its use list.
    @End Reasoning

    Let use_map be proc omap_create from OMap
    If cfg_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return use_map
    End If

    Let blocks be proc get_mir_cfg_blocks from CFG with cfg_ptr
    If blocks is equal to 0:
        Return use_map
    End If
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc get from List with blocks, i
        If block is not equal to 0:
            Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with block
            If instructions is not equal to 0:
                Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions
                Let j be 0
                While j is less than inst_count:
                    Let inst be proc get from List with instructions, j
                    If inst is not equal to 0:
                        proc record_instruction_uses with use_map, inst
                    End If
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return use_map
End Process

Process called "record_instruction_uses" that takes use_map as Integer, inst as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Adds inst to the use list of each value it reads. Used values come from
    the canonical enumerator (header operands + phi incomings) plus the
    call-family argument list (which the enumerator does not include) and the
    indirect callee. Each value's use list is an append-only List created
    lazily on first use.
    @End Reasoning

    Let used_values be proc get_instruction_used_values from CFG with inst
    If used_values is not equal to 0:
        Let used_count be proc length from List with used_values
        Let k be 0
        While k is less than used_count:
            Let v be proc get from List with used_values, k
            If v is not equal to 0:
                proc add_use with use_map, v, inst
            End If
            Set k to k plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with used_values
    End If

    Let opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with inst
    Let has_arg_list be 0
    If opcode is equal to 20304:
        Set has_arg_list to 1
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20305:
        Set has_arg_list to 1
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20700:
        Set has_arg_list to 1
    End If
    If has_arg_list is equal to 1:
        If opcode is equal to 20305:
            Let callee be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst, 80
            If callee is not equal to 0:
                proc add_use with use_map, callee, inst
            End If
        End If
        Let arguments be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst, 88
        If arguments is not equal to 0:
            Let arg_count be proc length from List with arguments
            Let a be 0
            While a is less than arg_count:
                Let av be proc get from List with arguments, a
                If av is not equal to 0:
                    proc add_use with use_map, av, inst
                End If
                Set a to a plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "add_use" that takes use_map as Integer, value_id as Integer, inst as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Appends inst to value_id's use list, creating the list lazily. The list is
    owned by the use_map and freed when the map is destroyed.
    @End Reasoning

    Let existing be proc omap_get from OMap with use_map, value_id
    If existing is equal to 0:
        Let new_list be proc list_create from List
        proc append from List with new_list, inst
        proc omap_set from OMap with use_map, value_id, new_list
    Otherwise:
        proc append from List with existing, inst
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: LATTICE TRANSITION
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "sccp_raise_lattice" that takes lattice_values as Integer, const_values as Integer, use_map as Integer, value_id as Integer, new_lattice as Integer, new_value as Integer, ssa_worklist as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Monotone lattice transition with SSA-use re-enqueueing. The lattice is
    UNKNOWN 0 -> CONSTANT 1 -> OVERDEFINED 2; a value never moves back down,
    and a CONSTANT recomputed to a DIFFERENT constant is raised to OVERDEFINED
    (this happens at join points and around loops). Every raise re-enqueues
    the instructions that USE the changed value so they re-evaluate with the
    new fact - that sparsity bounds the total work at two raises per value,
    guaranteeing termination.

    Returns 1 when the lattice changed, 0 otherwise.
    @End Reasoning

    If value_id is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let old_lattice be proc omap_get from OMap with lattice_values, value_id
    Let changed be 0

    If new_lattice is greater than old_lattice:
        proc omap_set from OMap with lattice_values, value_id, new_lattice
        If new_lattice is equal to 1:
            proc omap_set from OMap with const_values, value_id, new_value
        End If
        Set changed to 1
    Otherwise:
        If new_lattice is equal to 1:
            If old_lattice is equal to 1:
                Let old_value be proc omap_get from OMap with const_values, value_id
                If old_value is not equal to new_value:
                    Note: Conflicting constants meet at OVERDEFINED
                    proc omap_set from OMap with lattice_values, value_id, 2
                    Set changed to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    If changed is equal to 1:
        Let uses be proc omap_get from OMap with use_map, value_id
        If uses is not equal to 0:
            Let use_count be proc length from List with uses
            Let u be 0
            While u is less than use_count:
                Let using_inst be proc get from List with uses, u
                proc append from List with ssa_worklist, using_inst
                Set u to u plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Return changed
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANT EVALUATORS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "evaluate_comparison_operation" that takes opcode as Integer, left as Integer, right as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Evaluates a comparison (EQ/NE/LT/LE/GT/GE, opcodes 20100-20105) of two
    proven-constant integer operands to 1 (true) or 0 (false).
    @End Reasoning

    If opcode is equal to 20100:
        If left is equal to right:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20101:
        If left is not equal to right:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20102:
        If left is less than right:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20103:
        If left is less than or equal to right:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20104:
        If left is greater than right:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20105:
        If left is greater than or equal to right:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "evaluate_binary_operation" that takes opcode as Integer, left as Integer, right as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Evaluates a binary arithmetic / bitwise op of two proven-constant
    operands. The caller (the SCCP evaluator) guarantees the fold-soundness
    preconditions: no divide/modulo by zero, no out-of-range shift count, and
    no right shift of a negative value (so arithmetic and logical right shifts
    agree). Those guards live in the evaluator, never here.
    @End Reasoning

    If opcode is equal to 20002:
        Return left plus right
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20003:
        Return left minus right
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20004:
        Return left multiplied by right
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20005:
        If right is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return left divided by right
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20006:
        If right is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return left modulo by right
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20010:
        Return left bitwise and right
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20011:
        Return left bitwise or right
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20012:
        Return left bitwise xor right
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20014:
        Return left shifted left by right
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20015:
        Return left shifted right by right
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20016:
        Return left shifted right by right
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PER-INSTRUCTION EVALUATION
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "evaluate_instruction_sccp" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer, inst as Integer, lattice_values as Integer, const_values as Integer, use_map as Integer, edge_worklist as Integer, ssa_worklist as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Evaluates one instruction under the current lattice. Terminators enqueue
    their reachable successor BLOCKS onto edge_worklist (constant conditions
    prune to the taken edge - Wegman-Zadeck conditional pruning). Value
    producers compute their result lattice via sccp_raise_lattice, which
    re-enqueues the value's uses on a change.
    @End Reasoning

    Let opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with inst
    Let result_id be proc get_mir_node_value_id from MIR with inst

    Note: MIR_JUMP (20302): single target always reachable
    If opcode is equal to 20302:
        Let jump_target_id be proc get_mir_jump_target_block from MIRNodes with inst
        Let jump_target be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, jump_target_id
        If jump_target is not equal to 0:
            proc append from List with edge_worklist, jump_target
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MIR_BRANCH (20301): constant condition prunes to the taken edge
    If opcode is equal to 20301:
        Let cond_id be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with inst, 1
        Let cond_lattice be proc omap_get from OMap with lattice_values, cond_id
        Let true_id be proc get_mir_branch_true_block from MIRNodes with inst
        Let false_id be proc get_mir_branch_false_block from MIRNodes with inst

        If cond_lattice is equal to 1:
            Let cond_value be proc omap_get from OMap with const_values, cond_id
            Let taken_id be false_id
            If cond_value is not equal to 0:
                Set taken_id to true_id
            End If
            Let taken_block be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, taken_id
            If taken_block is not equal to 0:
                proc append from List with edge_worklist, taken_block
            End If
        Otherwise:
            If cond_lattice is equal to 2:
                Let true_block be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, true_id
                If true_block is not equal to 0:
                    proc append from List with edge_worklist, true_block
                End If
                Let false_block be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, false_id
                If false_block is not equal to 0:
                    proc append from List with edge_worklist, false_block
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MIR_SWITCH (20306): constant scrutinee selects one case/default
    If opcode is equal to 20306:
        Let switch_value_id be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with inst, 1
        Let switch_lattice be proc omap_get from OMap with lattice_values, switch_value_id
        Let case_count be proc get_switch_case_count from MIRNodes with inst
        Let default_id be proc get_switch_default_block from MIRNodes with inst

        If switch_lattice is equal to 1:
            Let scrutinee be proc omap_get from OMap with const_values, switch_value_id
            Let matched_id be default_id
            Let ci be 0
            While ci is less than case_count:
                Let case_value be proc get_switch_case_value from MIRNodes with inst, ci
                If case_value is equal to scrutinee:
                    Set matched_id to proc get_switch_case_block from MIRNodes with inst, ci
                    Set ci to case_count
                End If
                Set ci to ci plus 1
            End While
            Let matched_block be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, matched_id
            If matched_block is not equal to 0:
                proc append from List with edge_worklist, matched_block
            End If
        Otherwise:
            If switch_lattice is equal to 2:
                Let ci2 be 0
                While ci2 is less than case_count:
                    Let cbid be proc get_switch_case_block from MIRNodes with inst, ci2
                    Let cblk be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, cbid
                    If cblk is not equal to 0:
                        proc append from List with edge_worklist, cblk
                    End If
                    Set ci2 to ci2 plus 1
                End While
                Let default_block be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, default_id
                If default_block is not equal to 0:
                    proc append from List with edge_worklist, default_block
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MIR_RETURN (20303) / MIR_THROW (20703): no successors, no result
    If opcode is equal to 20303 or opcode is equal to 20703:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MIR_CONST (20001): numeric payload at extended offset 80
    If opcode is equal to 20001:
        Let is_string_const be proc is_const_string from MIRNodes with inst
        If is_string_const is equal to 1:
            proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 2, 0, ssa_worklist
        Otherwise:
            Let const_value be proc get_const_value from MIRNodes with inst
            proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 1, const_value, ssa_worklist
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MIR_COPY (20008): dest takes the source's lattice value
    If opcode is equal to 20008:
        Let src_id be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with inst, 1
        Let src_lattice be proc omap_get from OMap with lattice_values, src_id
        If src_lattice is equal to 1:
            Let src_value be proc omap_get from OMap with const_values, src_id
            proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 1, src_value, ssa_worklist
        Otherwise:
            If src_lattice is equal to 2:
                proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 2, 0, ssa_worklist
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MIR_PHI (20300): meet of incoming values. An incoming that is
    Note: UNKNOWN contributes nothing yet; CONSTANTs with the same value meet
    Note: at that constant, differing values meet at OVERDEFINED.
    If opcode is equal to 20300:
        Let incoming_count be proc get_phi_incoming_count from MIRNodes with inst
        Let phi_lattice be 0
        Let phi_value be 0
        Let pi be 0
        While pi is less than incoming_count:
            Let in_value be proc get_phi_incoming_value from MIRNodes with inst, pi
            Let in_lattice be proc omap_get from OMap with lattice_values, in_value
            If in_lattice is equal to 2:
                Set phi_lattice to 2
                Set pi to incoming_count
            Otherwise:
                If in_lattice is equal to 1:
                    Let in_const be proc omap_get from OMap with const_values, in_value
                    If phi_lattice is equal to 0:
                        Set phi_lattice to 1
                        Set phi_value to in_const
                    Otherwise:
                        If phi_lattice is equal to 1:
                            If phi_value is not equal to in_const:
                                Set phi_lattice to 2
                                Set pi to incoming_count
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            Set pi to pi plus 1
        End While
        If phi_lattice is equal to 1:
            proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 1, phi_value, ssa_worklist
        Otherwise:
            If phi_lattice is equal to 2:
                proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 2, 0, ssa_worklist
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Unary negation (20007) / bitwise not (20013): operand1 only
    If opcode is equal to 20007 or opcode is equal to 20013:
        Let unary_op_id be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with inst, 1
        Let unary_lattice be proc omap_get from OMap with lattice_values, unary_op_id
        If unary_lattice is equal to 1:
            Let unary_in be proc omap_get from OMap with const_values, unary_op_id
            Let unary_out be 0 minus unary_in
            If opcode is equal to 20013:
                Set unary_out to 0 minus unary_in minus 1
            End If
            proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 1, unary_out, ssa_worklist
        Otherwise:
            If unary_lattice is equal to 2:
                proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 2, 0, ssa_worklist
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Two-operand arithmetic / bitwise / comparison bands
    Let is_two_operand be 0
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20002 and opcode is less than or equal to 20006:
        Set is_two_operand to 1
    End If
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20010 and opcode is less than or equal to 20016:
        If opcode is not equal to 20013:
            Set is_two_operand to 1
        End If
    End If
    Let is_comparison be 0
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20100 and opcode is less than or equal to 20105:
        Set is_comparison to 1
        Set is_two_operand to 1
    End If

    If is_two_operand is equal to 1:
        Let operand1_id be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with inst, 1
        Let operand2_id be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with inst, 2
        Let lattice1 be proc omap_get from OMap with lattice_values, operand1_id
        Let lattice2 be proc omap_get from OMap with lattice_values, operand2_id

        If lattice1 is equal to 2 or lattice2 is equal to 2:
            proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 2, 0, ssa_worklist
            Return 1
        End If

        If lattice1 is equal to 1 and lattice2 is equal to 1:
            Let const1 be proc omap_get from OMap with const_values, operand1_id
            Let const2 be proc omap_get from OMap with const_values, operand2_id

            If is_comparison is equal to 1:
                Let cmp_result be proc evaluate_comparison_operation with opcode, const1, const2
                proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 1, cmp_result, ssa_worklist
                Return 1
            End If

            Note: Fold-soundness guards (match try_fold_instruction): no
            Note: division/modulo by zero, no out-of-range shift count, no
            Note: right shift of a negative value. A blocked fold raises the
            Note: result to OVERDEFINED so it is never silently treated as a
            Note: constant.
            Let can_fold be 1
            If opcode is equal to 20005 or opcode is equal to 20006:
                If const2 is equal to 0:
                    Set can_fold to 0
                End If
            End If
            If opcode is greater than or equal to 20014 and opcode is less than or equal to 20016:
                If const2 is less than 0:
                    Set can_fold to 0
                End If
                If const2 is greater than 63:
                    Set can_fold to 0
                End If
            End If
            If opcode is equal to 20015 or opcode is equal to 20016:
                If const1 is less than 0:
                    Set can_fold to 0
                End If
            End If

            If can_fold is equal to 0:
                proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 2, 0, ssa_worklist
                Return 1
            End If

            Let result_value be proc evaluate_binary_operation with opcode, const1, const2
            proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 1, result_value, ssa_worklist
            Return 1
        End If

        Note: Otherwise result remains UNKNOWN
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: All other value producers (loads, calls, allocas, type-dependent
    Note: casts, ...) are conservatively OVERDEFINED. Result-less instructions
    Note: (result_id 0) are skipped.
    If result_id is not equal to 0:
        proc sccp_raise_lattice with lattice_values, const_values, use_map, result_id, 2, 0, ssa_worklist
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: APPLICATION PHASE
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "is_pure_sccp_operation" that takes opcode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Only pure value computations may be rewritten to a constant: arithmetic
    and bitwise (20002-20016), comparisons (20100-20105), casts (20400-20408),
    and MIR_COPY (20008). Calls, loads, atomics, and terminators keep their
    side effects even when their result is provably constant.
    @End Reasoning

    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20002 and opcode is less than or equal to 20016:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20100 and opcode is less than or equal to 20105:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20400 and opcode is less than or equal to 20408:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "remove_phi_incomings_from_pred" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer, block_id as Integer, removed_pred as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    When a constant-branch fold removes the CFG edge pred -> block_id, every
    phi in block_id loses the incoming that flowed from pred: its (value,
    predecessor) pair must be deleted entirely, not merely renumbered. Leaving
    a stale incoming whose predecessor is no longer in the block's predecessor
    list breaks the SSA verifier's phi-completeness check (the incoming block
    must be a member of the predecessor list).

    Phi incoming pairs live in the flat pair List at extended offset 80
    (block at slot 2N, value at slot 2N+1) with the count at offset 88 (OD-1).
    We rebuild the pair List keeping only the pairs whose predecessor is not
    removed_pred, then write the shrunk List and the updated count back. Phi
    nodes are at the front of the block, so the scan stops at the first
    non-phi instruction.

    Returns the number of phi incomings removed.
    @End Reasoning

    Let block_ptr be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, block_id
    If block_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with block_ptr
    If instructions is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions
    Let removed be 0

    Let ii be 0
    While ii is less than inst_count:
        Let inst be proc get from List with instructions, ii
        Let opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with inst
        If opcode is equal to 20300:
            Let pairs be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst, 80
            Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst, 88
            If pairs is not equal to 0:
                Let kept be proc list_create from List
                Let kept_count be 0
                Let p be 0
                While p is less than count:
                    Let block_slot be p multiplied by 2
                    Let value_slot be block_slot plus 1
                    Let pair_pred be proc get from List with pairs, block_slot
                    Let pair_value be proc get from List with pairs, value_slot
                    If pair_pred is equal to removed_pred:
                        Set removed to removed plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        proc append from List with kept, pair_pred
                        proc append from List with kept, pair_value
                        Set kept_count to kept_count plus 1
                    End If
                    Set p to p plus 1
                End While
                proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with inst, 80, kept
                proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with inst, 88, kept_count
                proc list_destroy from List with pairs
            End If
            Set ii to ii plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set ii to inst_count
        End If
    End While

    Return removed
End Process

Process called "apply_sccp_results" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer, lattice_values as Integer, const_values as Integer, reachable_blocks as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Applies the converged lattice to the IR:
    1. Every reachable block's pure value producer whose result is a proven
       CONSTANT is replaced with a fresh canonical MIR_CONST record carrying
       the same result value id (an in-place rewrite is size-illegal: a
       104-byte binary record cannot become a 112-byte const).
    2. Every reachable conditional MIR_BRANCH whose condition is a proven
       CONSTANT is rewritten to a fresh unconditional MIR_JUMP to the taken
       block, and the un-taken CFG edge plus the un-taken successor's phi
       predecessor are removed.

    Unreachable blocks are left structurally in place here (the subsequent
    DCE / simplify_cfg passes remove blocks the constant-branch folding has
    orphaned, using the canonical block remover that owns the block_count
    cache); SCCP's job is the value and edge facts.

    Returns the count of rewrites performed (constants + folded branches).
    @End Reasoning

    Let blocks be proc get_mir_cfg_blocks from CFG with cfg_ptr
    If blocks is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    Let rewrites be 0

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc get from List with blocks, i
        If block is not equal to 0:
            Let block_id be proc get_mir_basic_block_id from CFG with block
            Let is_reachable be proc omap_get from OMap with reachable_blocks, block_id

            If is_reachable is not equal to 0:
                Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with block
                Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

                Let j be 0
                While j is less than inst_count:
                    Let inst be proc get from List with instructions, j
                    Let opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with inst

                    Note: --- Constant value replacement ---
                    Let result_id be proc get_mir_node_value_id from MIR with inst
                    If result_id is not equal to 0:
                        Let lattice be proc omap_get from OMap with lattice_values, result_id
                        If lattice is equal to 1:
                            Let is_pure be proc is_pure_sccp_operation with opcode
                            If is_pure is equal to 1:
                                If opcode is not equal to 20001:
                                    Let const_value be proc omap_get from OMap with const_values, result_id
                                    Let result_type be proc get_mir_node_type from MIR with inst
                                    Let const_inst be proc create_mir_const from MIRNodes with result_id, const_value, result_type, 0, 0
                                    If const_inst is not equal to 0:
                                        Let parent_block be proc get_mir_node_parent_block from MIR with inst
                                        proc set_mir_node_parent_block from MIR with const_inst, parent_block
                                        proc list_set from List with instructions, j, const_inst
                                        Set rewrites to rewrites plus 1
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If

                    Note: --- Constant-branch folding to an unconditional jump ---
                    If opcode is equal to 20301:
                        Let cond_id be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with inst, 1
                        Let cond_lattice be proc omap_get from OMap with lattice_values, cond_id
                        If cond_lattice is equal to 1:
                            Let cond_value be proc omap_get from OMap with const_values, cond_id
                            Let true_id be proc get_mir_branch_true_block from MIRNodes with inst
                            Let false_id be proc get_mir_branch_false_block from MIRNodes with inst
                            Let taken_id be false_id
                            Let dropped_id be true_id
                            If cond_value is not equal to 0:
                                Set taken_id to true_id
                                Set dropped_id to false_id
                            End If

                            Let jump_inst be proc create_mir_jump from MIRNodes with taken_id
                            If jump_inst is not equal to 0:
                                Let parent_block be proc get_mir_node_parent_block from MIR with inst
                                proc set_mir_node_parent_block from MIR with jump_inst, parent_block
                                proc list_set from List with instructions, j, jump_inst

                                Note: Drop the un-taken edge and the matching
                                Note: phi incoming pair in the un-taken
                                Note: successor, unless both edges go to the
                                Note: same block (then the edge stays live)
                                If dropped_id is not equal to taken_id:
                                    proc remove_cfg_edge from CFG with cfg_ptr, block_id, dropped_id
                                    proc remove_phi_incomings_from_pred with cfg_ptr, dropped_id, block_id
                                End If
                                Set rewrites to rewrites plus 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If

                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Constant-branch folding can invalidate the cached dominance facts
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cfg_ptr, 56, 0
    Return rewrites
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MAIN PASS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "optimize_function_with_sccp" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Full Wegman-Zadeck SCCP over one function's CFG.

    **ALGORITHM:**
    1. Initialize every SSA result to UNKNOWN (absent from the lattice map).
    2. Seed the edge worklist with the entry block.
    3. Drain both worklists to a fixed point:
       - EDGE worklist: mark the popped block reachable (first time only) and
         enqueue all its instructions onto the SSA worklist.
       - SSA worklist: evaluate each instruction; terminators enqueue reachable
         successor blocks, value producers raise lattice facts (which re-enqueue
         their uses).
    4. Apply: replace constant pure producers with MIR_CONST, fold constant
       conditional branches to jumps, drop pruned edges.

    Returns 1 when any rewrite was applied, 0 otherwise (the pass-manager
    change indicator).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    All maps are integer-keyed ordered maps (collections/dictionary
    string-hashes integer keys -> crash, Wave 3). lattice_values maps value id
    -> lattice level; const_values maps value id -> proven constant;
    reachable_blocks maps block id -> 1; use_map maps value id -> use list
    (built once up front for sparse re-enqueueing).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    The fixed point performs at most two lattice raises per value and visits
    each reachable instruction a bounded number of times, so the pass is
    effectively linear in instruction count plus uses. Run before DCE so the
    orphaned blocks and dead computations SCCP exposes are swept.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Operates purely on compiler-internal MIR. The CFG pointer may be null
    (guarded). Constant folding obeys the divide/shift soundness guards;
    branch folding removes only the provably un-taken edge. Worst-case failure
    on malformed IR is a missed optimization, never an unsafe write.
    @End Security_Scope

    If cfg_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let blocks be proc get_mir_cfg_blocks from CFG with cfg_ptr
    If blocks is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    If block_count is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let lattice_values be proc omap_create from OMap
    Let const_values be proc omap_create from OMap
    Let reachable_blocks be proc omap_create from OMap
    Let use_map be proc build_use_map with cfg_ptr
    Let ssa_worklist be proc list_create from List
    Let edge_worklist be proc list_create from List

    Note: Seed the edge worklist with the entry block (canonical entry slot;
    Note: fall back to the first registered block when never stamped)
    Let entry_block be proc get_cfg_entry_block from MIR with cfg_ptr
    If entry_block is equal to 0:
        Set entry_block to proc get from List with blocks, 0
    End If
    proc append from List with edge_worklist, entry_block

    Note: Fixed-point worklist algorithm
    While proc length from List with edge_worklist is greater than 0 or proc length from List with ssa_worklist is greater than 0:
        While proc length from List with edge_worklist is greater than 0:
            Let block be proc list_remove from List with edge_worklist, 0
            Let block_id be proc get_mir_basic_block_id from CFG with block
            Let already be proc omap_get from OMap with reachable_blocks, block_id
            If already is equal to 0:
                proc omap_set from OMap with reachable_blocks, block_id, 1
                Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with block
                Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions
                Let j be 0
                While j is less than inst_count:
                    Let inst be proc get from List with instructions, j
                    proc append from List with ssa_worklist, inst
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End While

        While proc length from List with ssa_worklist is greater than 0:
            Let inst2 be proc list_remove from List with ssa_worklist, 0
            proc evaluate_instruction_sccp with cfg_ptr, inst2, lattice_values, const_values, use_map, edge_worklist, ssa_worklist
        End While
    End While

    Note: Apply the converged facts to the IR
    Let rewrites be proc apply_sccp_results with cfg_ptr, lattice_values, const_values, reachable_blocks

    Note: Release pass-local state
    proc free_use_map with use_map
    proc omap_destroy from OMap with lattice_values
    proc omap_destroy from OMap with const_values
    proc omap_destroy from OMap with reachable_blocks
    proc list_destroy from List with ssa_worklist
    proc list_destroy from List with edge_worklist

    Let rewrites_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with rewrites
    Display "sccp: applied " joined with rewrites_str joined with " constant/branch rewrites"

    If rewrites is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "free_use_map" that takes use_map as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Frees every per-value use List inside the use_map, then the map itself.
    The lists are owned by the map (created lazily in add_use).
    @End Reasoning

    If use_map is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entry be proc omap_first from OMap with use_map
    While entry is not equal to 0:
        Let lst be proc omap_entry_value from OMap with entry
        If lst is not equal to 0:
            proc list_destroy from List with lst
        End If
        Set entry to proc omap_entry_next from OMap with entry
    End While
    proc omap_destroy from OMap with use_map
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "run_sccp_pass" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Pass-manager-facing entry point. mir_optimizer.runa's optimize_sccp
    wrapper extracts the CFG from the shared OptimizerContext (offset 0) and
    calls this with the CFG pointer directly, signalling mark_changed when
    this returns 1.

    Returns 1 if any rewrite was applied, 0 otherwise.
    @End Reasoning

    Return proc optimize_function_with_sccp with cfg_ptr
End Process

Process called "should_run_sccp" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Gate predicate. Refuses null or empty CFGs; otherwise always worth running
    (straight-line code with constant operands folds, and a single constant
    branch can prune an entire subgraph).

    Returns 1 when the pass should run, 0 otherwise.
    @End Reasoning

    If cfg_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let blocks be proc get_mir_cfg_blocks from CFG with cfg_ptr
    If blocks is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    If block_count is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "get_sccp_pass_name" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Short pass name for the pass-manager registration table and log header.
    @End Reasoning

    Return "Sparse Conditional Constant Propagation"
End Process

Process called "get_sccp_pass_description" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Human-readable pass description for diagnostics and pass-list rendering.
    @End Reasoning

    Return "Wegman-Zadeck SCCP: constant propagation with conditional-branch pruning"
End Process
